invalid PEM, valid token, expired token, non-RSA signing, malformed header, missing header, MaxBodySize wrapping\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/server.go` (88 lines)\n\n- `NewServer()` initializes AuthManager, loads public key (fatal-exits on failure)\n- `registerRoutes()` applies `AuthMiddleware` to `/api` route group; `/health` remains public\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/types.go`\n\n- Constants: `PublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`, `MaxBodySize = 32 << 20` (32 MiB)\n\n**Dependency:** `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` v5.2.1 (declared in `go.mod`)\n\n### Other JWT references in the codebase\n\n- **AR-011** (`changes/AR-011/`): Router-side JWT signing and authentication (complementary to AR-017's PicoD verification)\n- **AR-016** (`changes/AR-016/tasks.md`): References JWT in test scenarios for PicoD file management API\n- **design.md**: Documents all `/api` routes as JWT-protected\n\n---\n\n## 4. Feature/Archive Tracking Files\n\nThe project uses a structured change-request system under `changes/` with **17 ARs** (AR-001 through AR-017). Each AR contains:\n\n- `proposal.md` -- Purpose, scope, impact analysis, alternatives, acceptance criteria\n- `design.md` -- Technical design, architecture diagrams, API contracts\n- `delta-spec.md` -- Normative requirements with Gherkin-style scenarios\n- `tasks.md` -- Implementation task breakdown with verification steps\n\n### All AR directories:\n\n| AR | Topic | Module |\n|----|-------|--------|\n| AR-001 through AR-010 | Various earlier features | Various |\n| AR-011 | Router JWT Authentication & Signing | pkg/router |\n| AR-012 through AR-015 | Various features | Various |\n| AR-016 | PicoD File Management API | pkg/picod |\n| **AR-017** | **PicoD JWT Middleware** | **pkg/picod** |\n\n### AR-017 Specific Files (PicoD JWT Middleware):\n\n| File | Path |